Owner Comment: Per Account Manager, Carl Jeuken, Based upon our contract we have with the refiner for the H2S treatment we are only responsible when the FO is treated and discharged under one BOL (contract page 10). This means that we are responsible for the product to be on spec up on arrival to a discharge port with not stops in between. BOL are typically (cargo discharge ports) for BOPEC in Bonaire of for Bahamas Free port BORCO terminal. Our contract does not mention any hop guaranty to secondary or any other terminal in the region. Unless the two above mentioned ones. Nether it is mentioned that we are giving guaranty to any terminal after discharging the product to the BOL destination. Seems that these cargoes have been discharged at BOPEC, reloaded and PDVSA wants us to cover the treatments costs under a different BOL which is in conflict with the ISLA contract.  I suggest to reply and inform them that they are falling out of the contractual boarders and we cannot guaranty any cargo ones the BOL has changed nor after discharging the product in a shore tank where do have not been monitoring or treated to guaranty the hop.
Dispute Coordinator Comment: Emailed Carl for update
